schemas.name: Order
schemas.desc:
An Order tracks the fulfillment of an Edit when delivered using the
legacy, non-component-based delivery.

Each Order is uniquely identified by an `order_id`, which is generated
by Google.

Externally, Orders can also be identified by partners using its `custom_id`
(when provided).

fields.name: earliestAvailStartTime
fields.desc:
Timestamp of the earliest start date of the Avails
linked to this Order.

fields.name: seasonName
fields.desc:
Default Season name,
usually in the language of the country of origin.
Only available for TV Edits
Example: "Googlers, The - A Brave New World".

fields.name: normalizedPriority
fields.desc: A simpler representation of the priority.

enum.name: NORMALIZED_PRIORITY_UNSPECIFIED
enum.desc:
Value could not be determined, please contact technical support if
it should.

enum.name: LOW_PRIORITY
enum.desc: A low-priority asset, typically from a library movie.

enum.name: HIGH_PRIORITY
enum.desc: A high-priority asset, typically from a new release or box office hit.

fields.name: orderId
fields.desc:
ID internally generated by Google to uniquely identify an Order.
Example: 'abcde12_x'

fields.name: videoId
fields.desc:
Google-generated ID identifying the video linked to this Order, once
delivered.
Example: 'gtry456_xc'.

fields.name: episodeName
fields.desc:
Default Episode name,
usually in the language of the country of origin.
Only available for TV Edits
Example: "Googlers, The - Pilot".

fields.name: countries
fields.desc:
Countries where the Order is available,
using the "ISO 3166-1 alpha-2" format (example: "US").

fields.name: legacyPriority
fields.desc:
Legacy Order priority, as defined by Google.
Example: 'P0'

fields.name: orderedTime
fields.desc: Timestamp when the Order was created.

fields.name: showName
fields.desc:
Default Show name,
usually in the language of the country of origin.
Only available for TV Edits
Example: "Googlers, The".

fields.name: customId
fields.desc:
ID that can be used to externally identify an Order.
This ID is provided by partners when submitting the Avails.
Example: 'GOOGLER_2006'

fields.name: approvedTime
fields.desc: Timestamp when the Order was approved.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: Type of the Edit linked to the Order.

enum.name: TITLE_TYPE_UNSPECIFIED
enum.desc:
Value could not be determined, please contact technical support if
it should.

enum.name: MOVIE
enum.desc: A movie picture.

enum.name: SEASON
enum.desc: A season of a TV show.

enum.name: EPISODE
enum.desc: An episode of a TV show.

enum.name: BUNDLE
enum.desc: A collection of movies, i.e. "Googlers 1 and Googlers, the return"

fields.name: channelId
fields.desc:
YouTube Channel ID that should be used to fulfill the Order.
Example: "UCRG64darCZhb".

fields.name: priority
fields.desc:
Order priority, as defined by Google.
The higher the value, the higher the priority.
Example: 90

fields.name: status
fields.desc: High-level status of the order.

enum.name: STATUS_UNSPECIFIED
enum.desc:
Value could not be determined, please contact technical support if
it should.

enum.name: STATUS_APPROVED
enum.desc: Approved by Google.

enum.name: STATUS_FAILED
enum.desc: Waiting for partner to re-deliver the asset after a rejection by Google.

enum.name: STATUS_PROCESSING
enum.desc: Waiting for Google to process the asset.

enum.name: STATUS_UNFULFILLED
enum.desc: Waiting for partner to deliver the asset.

enum.name: STATUS_NOT_AVAILABLE
enum.desc: Used when Status is not available (i.e: Orders for TV Seasons).

fields.name: studioName
fields.desc: Name of the studio that owns the Edit ordered.

fields.name: receivedTime
fields.desc: Timestamp when the Order was fulfilled.

fields.name: channelName
fields.desc:
YouTube Channel Name that should be used to fulfill the Order.
Example: "Google_channel".

fields.name: rejectionNote
fields.desc:
Field explaining why an Order has been rejected.
Example: "Trailer audio is 2ch mono, please re-deliver in stereo".

fields.name: pphName
fields.desc: Name of the post-production house that manages the Edit ordered.

fields.name: statusDetail
fields.desc: Detailed status of the order

enum.name: ORDER_STATUS_UNSPECIFIED
enum.desc:
Value could not be determined, please contact technical support if
it should.

enum.name: ORDER_STATUS_QC_APPROVED
enum.desc: Approved by Google's Quality Control team.

enum.name: ORDER_STATUS_QC_REJECTION
enum.desc: Rejected by Google's Quality Control team, pending partner redelivery.

enum.name: ORDER_STATUS_INTERNAL_FIX
enum.desc: Internal error while processing the Order.

enum.name: ORDER_STATUS_OPEN_ORDER
enum.desc: Waiting for initial delivery from partner.

enum.name: ORDER_STATUS_NOT_AVAILABLE
enum.desc: Used on Orders that do not have Status, like TV Seasons.

enum.name: ORDER_STATUS_AWAITING_REDELIVERY
enum.desc: Waiting for re-delivery from partner.

enum.name: ORDER_STATUS_READY_FOR_QC
enum.desc:
Asset was delivered by partner, but is being reviewed by Google's
Quality Control team.

enum.name: ORDER_STATUS_FILE_PROCESSING
enum.desc: Waiting for Google to process the asset.

schemas.name: Avail
schemas.desc:
An Avail describes the Availability Window of a specific Edit in a given
country, which means the period Google is allowed to sell or rent the Edit.

Avails are exposed in EMA format Version 1.6b (available at
http://www.movielabs.com/md/avails/)

Studios can see the Avails for the Titles they own.
Post-production houses cannot see any Avails.

fields.name: storeLanguage
fields.desc:
Spoken language of the intended audience.
Language shall be encoded in accordance with RFC 5646.
Example: "fr".

fields.name: priceValue
fields.desc:
Value to be applied to the pricing type.
Example: "4" or "2.99"

fields.name: suppressionLiftDate
fields.desc:
First date an Edit could be publically announced as becoming
available at a specific future date in territory of Avail.
*Not* the Avail start date or pre-order start date.
Format is YYYY-MM-DD.
Only available for pre-orders.
Example: "2012-12-10"

fields.name: seasonAltId
fields.desc:
Other identifier referring to the season, as defined by partner.
Only available on TV avails.
Example: "rs_googlers_s1".

fields.name: captionIncluded
fields.desc: Communicating if caption file will be delivered.

fields.name: formatProfile
fields.desc: Indicates the format profile covered by the transaction.

enum.name: FORMAT_PROFILE_UNSPECIFIED
enum.desc:
Value could not be determined, please contact technical support if
it should.

enum.name: SD
enum.desc: Standard-definition format.

enum.name: HD
enum.desc: High-definition format.

enum.name: UHD
enum.desc: 4K UHD.

fields.name: contentId
fields.desc:
Title Identifier. This should be the Title Level EIDR.
Example: "10.5240/1489-49A2-3956-4B2D-FE16-5".

fields.name: displayName
fields.desc:
The name of the studio that owns the Edit referred in the Avail.
This is the equivalent of `studio_name` in other resources, but it follows
the EMA nomenclature.
Example: "Google Films".

fields.name: encodeId
fields.desc:
Manifestation Identifier. This should be the Manifestation
Level EIDR.
Example: "10.2340/1489-49A2-3956-4B2D-FE16-7"

fields.name: end
fields.desc:
End of term in YYYY-MM-DD format in the timezone of the country
of the Avail.
"Open" if no end date is available.
Example: "2019-02-17"

fields.name: pphNames
fields.desc:
Name of the post-production houses that manage the Avail.
Not part of EMA Specs.

fields.name: seriesAltId
fields.desc:
Other identifier referring to the series, as defined by partner.
Only available on TV avails.
Example: "rs_googlers".

fields.name: altId
fields.desc:
Other identifier referring to the Edit, as defined by partner.
Example: "GOOGLER_2006"

fields.name: episodeNumber
fields.desc:
The number assigned to the episode within a season.
Only available on TV Avails.
Example: "3".

fields.name: episodeAltId
fields.desc:
Other identifier referring to the episode, as defined by partner.
Only available on TV avails.
Example: "rs_googlers_s1_3".

fields.name: workType
fields.desc: Work type as enumerated in EMA.

enum.name: TITLE_TYPE_UNSPECIFIED
enum.desc:
Value could not be determined, please contact technical support if
it should.

enum.name: MOVIE
enum.desc: A movie picture.

enum.name: SEASON
enum.desc: A season of a TV show.

enum.name: EPISODE
enum.desc: An episode of a TV show.

enum.name: BUNDLE
enum.desc: A collection of movies, i.e. "Googlers 1 and Googlers, the return"

fields.name: releaseDate
fields.desc:
Release date of the Title in earliest released territory.
Typically it is just the year, but it is free-form as per EMA spec.
Examples: "1979", "Oct 2014"

fields.name: productId
fields.desc:
Edit Identifier. This should be the Edit Level EIDR.
Example: "10.2340/1489-49A2-3956-4B2D-FE16-6"

fields.name: captionExemption
fields.desc:
Communicating an exempt category as defined by FCC regulations.
It is not required for non-US Avails.
Example: "1"

fields.name: seasonTitleInternalAlias
fields.desc:
Title used by involved parties to refer to this season.
Only available on TV Avails.
Example: "Googlers, The".

fields.name: priceType
fields.desc:
Type of pricing that should be applied to this Avail
based on how the partner classify them.
Example: "Tier", "WSP", "SRP", or "Category".

fields.name: licenseType
fields.desc: Type of transaction.

enum.name: LICENSE_TYPE_UNSPECIFIED
enum.desc:
Value could not be determined, please contact technical support if
it should.

enum.name: EST
enum.desc: Electronic Sell Through - purchase policy for unlimited viewing.

enum.name: VOD
enum.desc: Video On Demand - rental policy for temporary viewing.

enum.name: SVOD
enum.desc:
Subscription Video On Demand - used for subscription platforms.
Not supported on Google Play.

enum.name: POEST
enum.desc: Pre-order Electronic Sell Through - pre-order purchase only window.

fields.name: seasonNumber
fields.desc:
The number assigned to the season within a series.
Only available on TV Avails.
Example: "1".

fields.name: ratingValue
fields.desc:
Value representing the rating.
Ratings should be formatted as per http://www.movielabs.com/md/ratings/
Example: "PG"

fields.name: availId
fields.desc:
ID internally generated by Google to uniquely identify an Avail.
Not part of EMA Specs.

fields.name: seriesTitleInternalAlias
fields.desc:
Title used by involved parties to refer to this series.
Only available on TV Avails.
Example: "Googlers, The".

fields.name: titleInternalAlias
fields.desc:
Title used by involved parties to refer to this content.
Example: "Googlers, The".
Only available on Movie Avails.

fields.name: ratingSystem
fields.desc:
Rating system applied to the version of title within territory
of Avail.
Rating systems should be formatted as per
[EMA ratings spec](http://www.movielabs.com/md/ratings/)
Example: "MPAA"

fields.name: territory
fields.desc:
ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code for the country or territory
of this Avail.
For Avails, we use Territory in lieu of Country to comply with
EMA specifications.
But please note that Territory and Country identify the same thing.
Example: "US".

fields.name: ratingReason
fields.desc:
Value representing the rating reason.
Rating reasons should be formatted as per
[EMA ratings spec](http://www.movielabs.com/md/ratings/)
and comma-separated for inclusion of multiple reasons.
Example: "L, S, V"

fields.name: episodeTitleInternalAlias
fields.desc:
OPTIONAL.TV Only. Title used by involved parties to refer to this episode.
Only available on TV Avails.
Example: "Coding at Google".

fields.name: videoId
fields.desc:
Google-generated ID identifying the video linked to this Avail, once
delivered.
Not part of EMA Specs.
Example: 'gtry456_xc'

fields.name: start
fields.desc:
Start of term in YYYY-MM-DD format in the timezone of the
country of the Avail.
Example: "2013-05-14".

fields.name: orders
fields.desc: List of Orders that match the request criteria.

fields.desc: See _List methods rules_ for more information about this field.

schemas.name: StoreInfo
schemas.desc:
Information about a playable sequence (video) associated with an Edit
and available at the Google Play Store.

Internally, each StoreInfo is uniquely identified by a `video_id`
and `country`.

Externally, Title-level EIDR or Edit-level EIDR, if provided,
can also be used to identify a specific title or edit in a country.

Knowledge Graph ID associated to this Edit, if available.

fields.name: seasonNumber

fields.name: seasonName

Default Season name, usually in the language of the country of
origin.
Only available for TV Edits
Example: "Googlers, The - A Brave New World".

fields.name: videoId

Google-generated ID identifying the video linked to the Edit.

fields.name: hasInfoCards

fields.name: subtitles

fields.name: country
